# 1 Control 1 — Recording Completeness: Automatic Call Recording Enforcement
### Description:
CIR is designed so that recording is triggered automatically at the application layer and is not dependent on end-user action within the application. Once a user is enabled for recording in Genesys Config Server, they are configured for 100% voice and screen recording by default. Unless an explicit policy has been defined in the recording configuration to limit the capture rate. There is no partial coverage by accident; any deviation from 100% is an intentional, configured decision.

As for user override capability, there is none. The recording playback and management portal has no functionality that allows any user, regardless of role, to modify or suppress a recording configuration. The only way to change whether a user is subject to recording is a direct change to that user's profile in Genesys Config Server, which is a privileged action managed exclusively by the Connect Operations team. I believe i did demonstrarte this live during our walkthrough. If you need additional evidence, please let me know what specially is needed. 


