# Control 3 — Recording Completeness: Real-Time Recording Failure Alert
Recording failure alerting operates at two levels. Infrastructure monitoring covering memory, disk, CPU and related thresholds is handled by the server team who manage and respond to those alerts as part of their standard operations. 

At the application level, Splunk Cloud is configured with alert rules that fire when specific conditions indicate a problem.

One example of an active alert is a rule that detects when no successful recordings have been received for a given client within the last 60 minutes. When that condition is met, Splunk automatically sends an email notification to the operations team identifying which client or clients are affected, giving them the opportunity to investigate and intervene before a more significant gap develops.

