# 6 Control 6 — Deletion Management: Restricted Deletion Rights
### Will probably need to clarify on Monday if the platform admin role has the abolity to delete objects from the recording buckets 

The recording portal does not expose any selective deletion capability regardless of user role. There is no option within the application for any user, including administrators, to manually delete individual recording files. Deletion in the context of this environment is handled exclusively through retention policies that are configured at the client level, meaning recordings are only removed when they reach the end of their defined retention period as a scheduled, policy-driven process rather than a manual action.

Outside of the application layer, cloud administrators do have the technical ability to delete encrypted media files directly from the GCP buckets. This access is tightly governed through GCP IAM policies and is limited to a small number of individuals within the cloud infrastructure team along with a handful of other authorized personnel. Access to the buckets is reviewed periodically as part of the organization's broader compliance obligations to ensure that only the appropriate individuals retain that level of access.

As evidence for this control we can provide the GCP IAM policy configuration showing which accounts hold bucket-level access, along with documentation of the client-level retention policy configuration demonstrating that deletion is policy-driven rather than manually initiated.
